			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If a program uses CHR ROM, and the mapper is NROM or something else incapable of bank switching CHR ROM, then the tiles are already available to the PPU from the moment the power is switched on.<br /><br />CHR RAM or bank switching would complicate things, as the program would have to do some setup in order to make the tiles available. In the case of bank switching, it would have to write bank numbers to the mapper's ports. In the case of CHR RAM, it would have to copy the tiles from PRG ROM to CHR RAM through the PPU.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

