				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Diskover wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How do I get sprite disappear from the screen? For example, when shooting touch the box, these two items disappear. How do I delete them?</div><br />Normally, game objects are placed into RAM slots. Game engines are made to support a certain number of active objects, and every frame these objects are updated and drawn. Deleting an object is just a matter of freeing up its slot, so the object will cease to exist and will not be updated or drawn anymore. Games with a constant number of objects, such as pong (which always has 2 paddles and 1 ball), can get away with having hardcoded objects, but any game that involve objects being created and destroyed dynamically needs to have some sort of object management.<br /><br />When a bullet hits an enemy, the common thing to do is destroy both objects (freeing up their slots) and create a new explosion object.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

